# React / TSX — condensed

Aligned with `.claude/rules/react-conventions.md` and coding-standards.

- **Complexity:** keep TSX branching within **cyclomatic complexity ≤ 11**; split sections or pure helpers before density hurts readability.
- **State/effects:** hooks for UI state; effects for real external sync — cleanup timers and subscriptions; avoid duplicating derive-able state.
- **Styling:** Tailwind utilities; match existing theme patterns; minimize ad-hoc inline styles.
- **Data:** flows through props and established loaders; persist domain behavior in the Supabase service layer per agents.md — not duplicated in leaves.

Full detail in `.claude/rules/react-conventions.md`.
